    <section>
        <h2>Energy Efficiency & Performance Improvement</h2>
        <p>
            Improving system performance requires a deep understanding of thermodynamics,
            component behavior and system interactions. The platform focuses on methods
            aimed at reducing energy consumption, minimizing losses and achieving
            measurable energy gains through optimized design and operation.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Methods & Engineering Approaches</h2>
        <p>
            Engineering approaches include system modeling, performance diagnostics,
            component-level analysis and global energy balance evaluation.
            These methods are applied to both existing installations and new system designs.
        </p>
    </section>

